    "excerpt": "A technical briefing on arXiv:2606.24643: Biancalana's Quantum Split-Step Fourier algorithm propagates classical mean field + Bogoliubov matrices U, V of quantum fluctuations through the same split-step integrator used in nonlinear Schrodinger simulations, then reconstructs symplectic eigenvalues, Williamson modes, and von Neumann entropy for any spectral window. Lossless Gaussian regime, exact diagnostics, low effective dimension even for radiation spanning many Fourier bins.",
