    "title": "Reading Loudon to improve a router â nine experiments, one ship",
    "slug": "loudon-photon-route-coherence-time",
    "excerpt": "Read Rodney Loudon's <em>Quantum Theory of Light</em> end-to-end to mine ideas for photon-route + meridian. Ten experiments grounded in chapters 3, 5, 6, and 9. Eight came back negative or decorative â squeezing was decorative, photon-number metric strictly weaker than Gaussian fidelity, non-Gaussian heralded states didn't survive the eval scale. One â a g<sup>(1)</sup> coherence-time feature â shipped to <code>meridian-orbital@3.1.0</code> with <strong>+108%</strong> discrimination over what it replaced. Honest accounting with every number.",
    "date": "May 9, 2026",
    "readingTime": "12 min read",
    "arxivLink": "https://ask-meridian.uk/blog/loudon-photon-route-coherence-time/",
