    "excerpt": "I tried to make Grok run my pharmacy errands end-to-end. The plan: search Ã¢â²' cart Ã¢â²' automated checkout, all chat-driven. The wall: VTEX's reCAPTCHA Enterprise enforces hostname binding server-side â your worker forwards a real captcha token, Google reports the origin doesn't match the site key, VTEX silently drops the email and returns <code>200 {}</code>. The pivot: anonymous cart in-worker + a <code>/checkout/cart/add</code> URL hand-off to the user's browser. Ships ~95% of the value without a Browserbase-class headless browser.",
