    "excerpt": "We just shipped <code>meridian-mcp</code> 2.0.0 to both registries from a single tag push. The honest tradeoff: anonymous install still requires npm, but for everything else GitHub Packages has earned its slot â auth shared with your code, automatic provenance, free private packages, same registry as your Docker images. The full release workflow + the <code>npm pkg set name</code> rename trick that lets one tarball ship under two names.",
