    "title": "Building a production MCP server on Cloudflare Workers (with auth + Stripe)",
    "slug": "production-mcp-server-cloudflare-workers",
    "excerpt": "Most MCP tutorials show <code>npx create-mcp</code> and a Hello-world tool. Real servers in production need auth, per-key quotas, billing, and an upgrade path. Here's the architecture we use for ask-meridian.uk â entirely on Cloudflare's free tier â and the specific gotchas you'll hit.",
