    "excerpt": "Most RAG systems either retrieve from a static corpus or end-to-end LLM-rank. Meridian does neither. Llama-3.3-70B authors fresh candidates per task; a deterministic JS classifier assigns each a celestial body class (planet/moon/trojan/asteroid/comet/irregular) based on physics-style features. Why the metaphor, why the deterministic step, and where it goes next.",
